<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>out in left field • out in the field</xh5><p> <i>out in left field</i>—(also: way out in left field) 1. <i>(of a person)</i> unusual and eccentric or out of contact with reality: Sally is a lot of fun, but she’s sort of <u>out in left field</u>. 2. <i>(of an idea, answer, etc.)</i> mistaken, strange and illogical: What he said was totally <u>out in left field</u>. He has no idea what we were talking about.</p><p> <i>out in the field—</i>on the warpath; ready for a fight or quarrel: I should keep away from there; her father is <u>out in the field</u> looking for trouble.</p> </entry>
